benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC29 cover successful creation with valid data and various parameter combinations.
Invalid Payload: @TC08 covers malformed request body; @TC11 covers invalid requestedDate format.
Missing Required Header: @TC09 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Missing Request Body: @TC10 covers absence of request body.
Invalid bundleId format: @TC06 covers invalid format; @TC07 covers non-existent bundleId.
No Data in System: @TC05 covers no bundles present.
Extra Unexpected Parameters: @TC12 covers handling of additional parameters.
Maximum/Minimum Values: @TC13 and @TC14 cover boundary testing.
Partial Input: @TC15 covers partial data in BlockingState.
Large Payload: @TC16 covers stress testing with large data.
Service Unavailability: @TC17 covers system down scenarios.
Authentication: @TC18 covers invalid/missing tokens.
Injection/XSS: @TC19 and @TC20 cover security testing.
Network Retry: @TC21 covers transient network errors and retries.
Concurrent Requests: @TC22 covers multiple simultaneous requests.
Special Characters: @TC23 covers special character handling.
Backward Compatibility: @TC24 covers legacy client support.
Performance: @TC25, @TC26, @TC27 cover response time and resource utilization under load.
Dependent Service Errors: @TC28 covers dependency failures.
Data Consistency: @TC29 covers system-wide data integrity.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized or forbidden access beyond missing header.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate rapid repeated requests to verify throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Retry Logic for Server Errors: No explicit tests for 500 errors or retries beyond network errors.
Accessibility: No tests for API documentation accessibility or usability.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to ensure large dataset responses are managed correctly.
Include explicit authorization tests to verify proper access control.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to prevent abuse.
Test caching headers and validation for cache invalidation.
Create scenarios for server error retries and fallback mechanisms.
Add accessibility testing for API documentation and error messages.
